<Layout title="Day Trips">
	<h1>Day Trips</h1>
	<p>
		A collection of easy half‑day and full‑day trips from Nardelli. Each section includes suggested timing and parking,
		and you can use the map at the bottom to explore pinned locations.
	</p>

	<h2>Nardelli Oil &amp; Wine</h2>
	<p>
		On our doorstep there is both an olive oil producer
		(<a href="https://cooperativaoleificiopozzuolese.it/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cooperativa Oleificio Pozzuolese</a>)
		and a winery (<a href="https://cantinagoccia.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cantina Goccia</a>).
		Both offer tasting tours individually, or you can book a combined{" "}
		<a href="https://cantinagoccia.com/wine-tour" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nardelli Experience</a>{" "}
		where you do both over ~2.5 hours.
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 hour – 2.5 hours</li>
		<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 minute</li>
		<li><strong>Parking:</strong> on site (or walk)</li>
	</ul>

	<img
		src="/photos/nardelli-olive-tree.jpg"
		alt="Olive tree near Nardelli"
		loading="lazy"
		style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
	/>

	<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Val d’Orcia (Half day / full day)</h2>
<p>
	The Val d’Orcia is classic Tuscany: rolling hills, cypress‑lined roads and picture‑perfect villages. It works brilliantly as a half‑day if you choose one stop,
	or a full day if you combine two or more towns (and allow time for a long lunch).
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day (one stop) or full day (2–4 stops)</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~25–60 minutes depending on the town</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> see each stop below</li>
</ul>
<!-- Optional: replace with a temporary web photo later -->
