<h3>Montepulciano</h3>
<p>
	A lively hill town with steep streets, great viewpoints and plenty of places to stop for lunch or a wine tasting. It is no wonder it is town that has been heavily used in the movies business. A good “anchor” stop in the Val d’Orcia if you want a full half‑day in one place,
	or an easy pairing with Pienza. Walking tours / wine tasting tours and visiting the viewpoint behind the Piazza Grande at sunset highly recommended. We have a tradition of getting a coffee or Vino Nobile in the goregous Caffè Poliziano (try to get a seat on the balcony). 
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day / full day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~25 minutes</li>
	<li>
		<strong>Recommended parking:</strong>{" "}
		<a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/wUnm6ZSEKGh1jCsj9" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps link</a>
	</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/MontepulcianoPanorama2.jpg/1920px-MontepulcianoPanorama2.jpg"
	alt="Montepulciano panorama"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
/>

<h3>Pienza</h3>
<p>
	A beautiful Renaissance town that’s perfect for a relaxed stroll, a coffee stop, and picking up local pecorino cheese. It’s compact, easy, and flat (unique in the area)
	which makes it a great half‑day option and easy to get around. Add‑on before Montepulciano / Montalcino to make it a full day trip.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~40 minutes (or ~20 minutes from Montepulciano)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="/photos/pienza.jpg"
	alt="Pienza"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
/>

<h3>Montalcino</h3>
<p>
	Famous for Brunello wine and big countryside views. It’s a great half‑day trip if you want a slower pace: a wander, a viewpoint, and a long lunch.
	It also pairs nicely with Pienza if you want a full day in the area.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 hour (or ~25 minutes from Pienza)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1f/Montalcino-Fortress.jpg"
	alt="Montalcino fortress"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
/>

<h3>Bagno Vignoni</h3>
<p>
	A tiny, unique stop built around its historic thermal waters. Even if you only spend a short time here, it’s a memorable place for photos and a gentle walk—
	great as a pairing with Pienza or Montalcino.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day (or add‑on stop)</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 hour (or ~20 minutes from Pienza / Montalcino)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Bagno_Vignoni_Piazza_delle_Sorgenti_01.jpg/1920px-Bagno_Vignoni_Piazza_delle_Sorgenti_01.jpg"
	alt="Bagno Vignoni thermal square"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
/>

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Passignano sul Trasimeno (Half day / full day)</h2>
<p>
	A relaxed lakeside town with a great promenade feel—ideal for a simple day by the water. Nice walks, coffees, drinks or playgroud visits (with kids) along the promenade. Visit the local pottery shops for a souvenier you will use when home. Works as a half‑day trip on its own,
	or make it a full day by adding a longer lakeside stop (e.g. Sualzo Beach / Pool).
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day / full day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~25 minutes</li>
	<li>
		<strong>Recommended parking:</strong>{" "}
		<a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/NaS1AxR4L4GKNswo8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps link</a>
	</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="/photos/PassignanoSulTrasimeno.jpeg"
	alt="Passignano sul Trasimeno"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
/>

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Isola Maggiore (Half day)</h2>
<p>
	A great half‑day escape on Lake Trasimeno. Take the ferry over, stroll through the small lanes, and enjoy a slow lunch by the water. Hike up the hill and around the island if you are more adventurous but bring plenty of water. 
	It’s an easy “holiday” feeling without any big drive.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~7 minutes to the ferry (plus ferry time)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD — near the ferry)</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Isola_Maggiore.jpg/1920px-Isola_Maggiore.jpg"
	alt="Isola Maggiore"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
/>

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Cortona (Half day)</h2>
<p>
	A beautiful Tuscan hill town known for views, steep streets, and a classic old‑town vibe. Great for browsing shops, a relaxed wander,
	and a long lunch if you time it right. LART UNIVERSE Palazzo Ferretti & Circle of Life Art Gallery are both worth a visit.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~30 minutes</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<img
	src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/bf/Cortona-vista01.jpg"
	alt="Cortona view"
	loading="lazy"
	style="width:100%; max-width:680px; display:block; margin: 12px auto 0; border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
